snippet.textDisplay: If I may just add a few thoughts - take or leave as you wish of course.  From my perspective -- this crisis should be  a "wake up call" but much  more to do with our treatment of animals than anything else.  The virus originated from consuming infected bats at a "wildlife farmer's market" in China.  That wildlife market had been written up a month ago by a travel writer for the NY Post who said it was a heartbreaking site.  Beautiful wildlife in cages on sale for slaughter.  Wildlife.
